<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n53123q"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53123q">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53123q"> 123(q)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Arata-/Kalama (sage), <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n53123q"><li>FW 59.23 </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/lexc.htm#n53123q">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/l39c.htm#n53123q">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n53123q">MS BL 47476b-177</ms> </li><li>JJA 49:375 <a name="cd10" href="../../ff/fdra/cda.htm#cd10">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/c/cd10.htm#n53123q">Draft: I.3&sect;1.10</a>/2.10/3.10</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Siddh&acirc;rtha &eacute;tait entr&eacute; dans l&apos;ermitage o&ugrave; <mark>le pieux Ar&acirc;ta-K&acirc;l&acirc;ma</mark> enseignait le renoncement &agrave; des disciples nombreux. Tous, en le voyant, l&apos;avaient admir&eacute;; partout o&ugrave; il passait, brillait une lumi&egrave;re merveilleuse; d&egrave;s qu&apos;il parlait, on l&apos;&eacute;coutait avec joie; sa voix &eacute;tait douce et forte, et il savait convaincre. <small> A. Ferdinand Herold, <a name="AFHB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#AFHB"><cite title="source">La Vie Du Bouddha</cite></a> (1922) 67f</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Siddharta spent some months living in a cell with the sage Arata-Kalama before wandering through the lands of Magadha, begging as he went. He visited the ashram of Roudaka and listened to his philosophy, but was unimpressed. Then he came to the river Nairanjana and he sat down and meditated and became as one who was dead. His mother, Maya, came down from heaven at this and she strewed his body with flowers and chided him for neglect.] </mm> </dd></dl>
